<subSubSection id="66162E203EF55A3A048292A89BFB6389" lastPageId="68" lastPageNumber="69" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="D1A185C1DFE308319F77F99792668CCE" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C04BA78EDAEB301BF759C9A91BB7DEE0" lastPageId="68" lastPageNumber="69" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">
This species shares male genitalic characters with several others in this group (
<taxonomicName id="34774F38A80F13F09D6915993AADE09C" class="Insecta" family="Histeridae" genus="Baconia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Baconia godmani" order="Coleoptera" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="godmani">Baconia godmani</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="36FE2F3A55306F6FF732AC1D5C741010" class="Insecta" family="Histeridae" genus="Baconia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Baconia rossi" order="Coleoptera" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rossi">Baconia rossi</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="28E7A89118FF009BD0FE9FE83DE6B5DF" class="Insecta" family="Histeridae" genus="Baconia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Baconia scintillans" order="Coleoptera" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scintillans">Baconia scintillans</taxonomicName>
), but is distinctive in its small size, parallel-sided form (Fig. 16B), presence of complete elytra striae 1-5, noncrenulate meso 
<pageBreakToken id="33D4224CBBDB593FB17A1608F1489031" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" start="start">metaventral</pageBreakToken>
stria (Fig. 16C), and series of punctures in place of both the basal propygidial stria (Fig. 16D) and the lateral submarginal pronotal stria.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
